ECB Nowotny Says Greece Decisions Need ‘Intact’ Rescue Umbrella

-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s   a n d   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-10-10T16:51:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/ecb-nowotny-says-greece-decisions-need-intact-rescue-umbrella.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Ewald Nowotny said rescue mechanisms must be
fully intact before decisions on  Greece  are made.  “It is very important that before anything is decided the
rescue umbrellas are completely intact,” Nowotny told reporters
in Vienna today. “Without a functioning rescue mechanism all
other measures are extremely risky.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss in Vienna at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
